snippet.title: 21 August 2025
snippet.description:
#Erode #Thalavadi #wildlife valparai news update#WildElephant #CCTVFootage #ElephantAlert #HumanWildlifeConflict #ElectricFence #ForestNews #WildlifeConservation #ElephantStories #TamilNadu

In Karalavadi village near Thalavadi in Erode district, a wild elephant attempted to enter the farm of a farmer named Saravanakumar after straying out of the forest.

On seeing the electric fence set up around the field, the elephant stood there for a long time. Realizing the danger of electrocution, it eventually retreated without entering the farmland.

This moment was clearly recorded on the CCTV camera installed there and is now being widely discussed on social media.

The elephant’s “alert” behavior, retreating after noticing the electric fence, has surprised the farmers of the area.

— Our Correspondent, Muruganandam
